The paper focuses on improving the recognition of security bugs through data mining and optimization techniques, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and computer security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of machine learning algorithms and hyperparameter optimization also suggests a potential fit for artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves data pre-processing and optimization, which could also be relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
